\pard\f0\fs28  Subgen. {\b Juncus.} Perennials. Leaves at base of stems, terete, non-septate, pungent, stem-like, with pith of rounded cells and vascular bundles distributed over most of the cross-section; stomata depressed. Auricles absent. Lowest two bracts leaf-like, pungent. Inflorescence usually apparently terminal. Involucral bracteoles absent. Seeds with appendages.
\par
