\pard\f0\fs28  {\b 5. J. heldreichianus} Marsson ex Parl., {\i Fl. Ital. }{\b 2}: 315 (1857). Like {\b 4} but stems usually 1·5-2·5 mm in diameter; inflorescence lax; lowest bract usually shorter than the inflorescence, the second short, the upper mostly with a small pungent lamina; flowers light brown; perianth-segments equal or subequal; anthers 1·5-2·2 mm; capsule 3-4(-4·5) mm, ovoid, conical to slightly angular at apex, often shortly mucronate, usually light brown; seeds 40-75, 1-1·5 mm; appendages unequal. 2n = 48.{\i  Salt-marshes, maritime sands and damp places inland. Greece and Aegean region.} Cr Gr Tu.
